'''Viktor Einar Gyökeres''' ({{IPA|sv|ˈvɪ̌kːtɔr ˈjø̂ːkɛrɛs|lang}};<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 July 2022 |title=Guess Who {{!}} Ben Wilson and Viktor Gyokeres |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ulq1V8nasr4&t=15s |access-date=18 November 2024 |website=[[YouTube]] |author=[[Coventry City F.C.]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=11 January 2019|title=Januariturnén 2019: Viktor Gyökeres|trans-title=January Tour 2019: Viktor Gyökeres|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RAm_ziUU_tA|access-date=28 November 2024|website=[[YouTube]]|publisher=FanTV|language=Swedish}}</ref> born 4 June 1998) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for {{English football updater|Arsenal}} club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

Gyökeres made his professional debut with Swedish side [[IF Brommapojkarna|Brommapojkarna]] in 2015, making over fifty appearances before joining [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in 2018. He spent successive seasons on loan at [[FC St. Pauli|St. Pauli]], [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]], and [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]], joining the latter permanently in 2021.

[[Sporting CP]] signed Gyökeres in 2023 in a club-record transfer worth an initial €20 million. With them, he won two back-to-back [[Primeira Liga]] titles in [[2023–24 Primeira Liga|2024]] and [[2024–25 Primeira Liga|2025]], winning the [[Bola de Prata (Portugal)|Bola de Prata]] as the league's top scorer, the [[LPFP Primeira Liga Player of the Year|Player of the Year]] award in both seasons and the [[Gerd Müller Trophy]], in his second season, given to the highest-scoring footballer in the previous season. In July 2025, he signed for Arsenal in a transfer worth €63.5 million (£54.8 million), winning the [[2025–26 Premier League|Premier League title]] in his first season as the club's top scorer.

Gyökeres represented Sweden at various youth levels and was the joint-top scorer at the [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]]. He made his senior debut in 2019.

==Club career==

=== IFK Aspudden-Tellus ===
Born and raised in [[Stockholm]], Gyökeres started playing football at the age of five with local club [[IFK Aspudden-Tellus]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mitti.se/nyheter/miljonregn-ska-gynna-de-unga-spelarna-i-fotbollsklubben-6.3.171194.b40c8ec321|title=Miljonregn ska gynna de unga spelarna i fotbollsklubben|date=2 September 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Renascença |date=6 March 2024 |title=Na pegada de Gyökeres em Estocolmo – Renascença V+ |url=https://rr.sapo.pt/video/bola-branca/2024/03/06/na-pegada-de-gyokeres-em-estocolmo/380020/ |access-date=6 March 2024 |website=rr.sapo.pt |language=pt-pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 July 2023 |title=Viktor Einar Gyökeres |url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/football/main-team/squad/viktor-einar-gyokeres |access-date=4 November 2024 |website=www.sporting.pt |language=en}}</ref>

===IF Brommapojkarna===
Gyökeres signed for [[IF Brommapojkarna|Brommapojkarna]] from [[IFK Aspudden-Tellus]] in 2013, at the age of 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cgj7lq6g38lo|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Sporting striker's rise to become one of Europe's best strikers|date=5 November 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He progressed through the youth teams and made his senior debut two years later.<ref name=IFB>{{cite web|url=http://ifbp.se/forening/viktor-gyokeres-klar-for-brighton-hove-albion-fc/|title=Viktor Gyökeres klar för Brighton & Hove Albion FC|trans-title=Viktor Gykeres ready for Brighton & Hove Albion FC|website=IF Brommapojkarna|last=Appelquist|first=Peter|date=6 September 2017|access-date=5 January 2018|language=sv}}</ref> He scored his first goals for the club on 20 August 2015, netting a brace in a 3–0 [[Svenska Cupen]] win over [[IF Sylvia]].<ref name="IFB" /> The following year, with the club having suffered relegation the season before, Gyökeres scored seven goals to help Brommapojkarna secure promotion back into the [[Superettan]].<ref name="AB">{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/dVJg1/stor-chans-att-vi-lyckas-med-det-ocksa|title="Stor chans att vi lyckas med det också..."|trans-title="Great chance we'll succeed too ..."Gyúkers make a success in BP – he will do the same for Sweden in the U19-EM|website=Afonbladet|last=Strandman|first=Pelle|date=2 July 2017|access-date=7 January 2018|language=sv}}</ref> He later helped Brommapojkarna into the semi-finals of the [[Svenska Cupen]] when he scored the winning goal in the quarter finals against top division side, [[IF Elfsborg|Elfsborg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/svenska-cupen-1/tv-18-aringen-skot-bp-till-stor-cupskrall-med-solomal/|title=TV: 18-åringen sköt BP till stor cupskräll med solomål
|trans-title=TV: 18-year-old shot BP to big cupboard with solstice|website=fotbollskanalen|last=Forsberg|first=Aron|date=12 March 2017|access-date=7 January 2018|language=sv}}</ref> Brommapojkarna were unable to progress further, though, as they were beaten 4–0 by [[IFK Norrköping]] in the next round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://svenskfotboll.se/cuper-och-serier/svenska-cupen-herrar/slutspel/?scr=result&fmid=3617935|title=Svenska Cupen, Slutspel Matchinformation IFK Norrköping FK mot IF Brommapojkarna|trans-title=Svenska Cupen Match Information IFK Norrköping FK v IF Brommapojkarna|date=19 March 2017|access-date=7 January 2018|language=sv}}</ref>

On 6 September 2017, having scored 10 league goals at the time, Gyökeres signed a two-and-a-half-year contract with [[Premier League]] side [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] with the deal to go through at the conclusion of the [[2017 Superettan|Superettan season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2017/september/albion-agree-deal-for-swedish-youngster/|title=Albion Agree Deal for Swedish Youngster|website=Brighton & Hove Albion|date=6 September 2017|access-date=5 January 2018|archive-date=7 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907165714/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2017/september/albion-agree-deal-for-swedish-youngster/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kwese.espn.com/football/soccer-transfers/story/3197938/brighton-agree-viktor-gyokeres-transfer-from-brommapojkarna-on-jan-1|title=Brighton agree Viktor Gyokeres transfer from Brommapojkarna|website=ESPN|date=6 September 2017|access-date=5 January 2018}}</ref> He ended the season with a return of 13 goals in 29 league appearances, including a [[hat-trick]] on the final day as Brommapojkarna secured promotion to the [[Allsvenskan]] as league champions.<ref name=TF>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/viktor-gyokeres-excited-joining-brighton-i-ll-start-with-u23s-4214348|title=Viktor Gyokeres excited joining Brighton: I'll start with U23s|website=Tribal Football|last=Vegas|first=Paul|date=3 January 2018|access-date=5 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=AL>{{cite web|url=http://ifbp.se/forening/seriesegern-sakrad-efter-gyokeres-avskedsshow/|title=Seriesegern säkrad efter Gyökeres avskedsshow|trans-title=Series victory secured after Gykeres farewell show|website=IF Brommapojkarna|date=4 November 2017|access-date=5 January 2018|last=Appelquist|first=Peter|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/superettan/tv-hattrick-av-gyokeres-i-avskedet---bp-klara-seriesegrare/|title=TV: Hattrick av Gyökeres i avskedet – BP klara seriesegrare|trans-title=TV: Hattrick of Gyøgeres in dismissal – BP clear series lover|website=fotbollskanalen|last=Ternstedt|first=Louis|date=4 November 2017|access-date=7 January 2018|language=sv}}</ref>

===Brighton & Hove Albion===
Gyökeres officially joined Brighton on 1 January 2018 and began training with the club's [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. Reserves and Academy|under-23]] side.<ref name=TF/> He made his senior debut for the club on 28 August, starting in a 1–0 [[EFL Cup]] defeat to [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sussexexpress.co.uk/sport/football/albion/brighton-knocked-out-of-carabao-cup-by-late-southampton-goal-1-8617070|title=Brighton knocked out of Carabao Cup by late Southampton goal|publisher=Sussex Express|last=Bailey|first=Steve|date=28 August 2018|access-date=29 August 2018}}</ref> On 26 January 2019, Gyökeres made his [[FA Cup]] debut coming on as a sub in a 0–0 draw at home to [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46928651|title=Brighton 0–0 West Brom in FA Cup fourth round|publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 January 2019|access-date=26 January 2019}}</ref>

In July 2019, he moved on loan to German second-tier side [[FC St. Pauli|St. Pauli]] for the 2019–20 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/news/published/gyoekeres-joins-on-loan/|title=Gyökeres joins on loan|website=FC St. Pauli|access-date=26 July 2019|archive-date=21 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121222035/https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/news/published/gyoekeres-joins-on-loan/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On the opening day of the [[2019–20 FC St. Pauli season|season]] he made his debut coming on as a sub in a 1–1 away draw to [[Arminia Bielefeld|Arminia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DSC ARMINIA BIELEFELD VS. FC ST. PAULI|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/matches/2019-2020-1-dsc-arminia-bielefeld-vs-fc-st-pauli/|access-date=31 August 2019|date=31 August 2019|archive-date=24 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230124224346/https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/matches/2019-2020-1-dsc-arminia-bielefeld-vs-fc-st-pauli/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Gyökeres scored his first goal for St Pauli on 29 September scoring the second in a 2–0 home victory over [[SV Sandhausen]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2019/2020 – 8. – FC St Pauli vs. SV Sandhausen – FC St Pauli|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/matches/2019-2020-8-fc-st-pauli-vs-sv-sandhausen/|access-date=30 September 2019|date=29 September 2019|archive-date=24 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230124224341/https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/matches/2019-2020-8-fc-st-pauli-vs-sv-sandhausen/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 17 September 2020, Gyökeres scored his first goal for Brighton in a 4–0 victory against [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] in the [[2020–21 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54097200|title= Brighton fringe players impress in win| work=BBC Sport | date=17 September 2020 | access-date=18 September 2020}}</ref> On 2 October 2020, Gyökeres joined [[EFL Championship]] side [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] on loan for the remainder of the [[2020–21 Swansea City A.F.C. season|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/1850663/viktor-gyokeres-heads-to-swansea-on-loan|title=Viktor Gyokeres heads to Swansea on loan|publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|date=2 October 2020|access-date=2 October 2020|archive-date=20 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211020083224/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/1850663/viktor-gyokeres-heads-to-swansea-on-loan|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut a day later, coming on as a substitute in a 2–1 home win over [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54305594|title= Swansea City 2–1: Millwall: Swans remain unbeaten after hard–fought win| work=BBC Sport | date=3 October 2020 | access-date=3 October 2020}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 9 January 2021, scoring the second in a 2–0 away win over [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]] sending Swansea through to the fourth round of the [[2020–21 FA Cup|FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55574474| publisher=BBC Sport |title= FA Cup: Stevenage 0–2 Swansea City – Wayne Routledge and Viktor Gyökeres send Swans through| access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref> He was recalled by Brighton on 14 January 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swanseacity.com/news/viktor-gyokeres-recalled-swansea-city-loan-spell|title=Viktor Gyokeres recalled from Swansea City loan spell &#124; Swansea|website=www.swanseacity.com}}</ref>

===Coventry City===
Gyökeres joined [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] on loan on 15 January 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.ccfc.co.uk/news/2021/january/transfer-viktor-gyokeres-joins-coventry-city-on-loan/|title=TRANSFER: Viktor Gyökeres joins Coventry City on loan!|publisher=Coventry City F.C.|date=15 January 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55677126|title=Coventry sign striker Gyokeres on loan|work=BBC Sport |date=15 January 2021 }}</ref> He made his debut four days later starting and playing 59 minutes of the 3–0 away loss at [[Reading F.C.|Reading]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/19023723.viktor-gyokeres-makes-debut-coventry/|title=On-loan Albion striker makes his debut for Coventry|date=20 January 2021|website=The Argus}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55627723| publisher=BBC Sport |title=Reading 3–0 Coventry City: Lucas Joao & John Swift lead Royals to victory| access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref> He scored on his first appearance at [[St Andrew's (stadium)|St Andrew's]] netting the first in an eventual 2–0 victory over [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]] on 27 January, his first league goal in English football.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55598374| publisher=BBC Sport |title=Coventry City 2–0 Sheffield Wednesday: Viktor Gyokeres & Jamie Allen gets goals| access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref>

He returned to Coventry City on a permanent deal on 9 July 2021, after signing a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coventrytelegraph.net/sport/football/transfer-news/coventry-city-transfers-viktor-gyokeres-20985651|title=Sky Blues sign Brighton striker Viktor Gyokeres|first=Andy|last=Turner|date=9 July 2021|website=CoventryLive}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57785110|title=Coventry sign Gyokeres on three-year deal|work=BBC Sport |date=9 July 2021 }}</ref> 
Gyökeres scored in Coventry's opening game of the [[2021–22 EFL Championship|2021–22 Championship season]] on 8 August, putting Coventry back level in an eventual 2–1 victory over [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in Coventry's first home game since April 2019 after ground sharing with [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58044188|title=Coventry City 2–1 Nottingham Forest: Late Kyle Mcfadzean makes magical Sky Blues home return|work=BBC Sport |date=8 August 2021|access-date=8 August 2021}}</ref> Gyökeres scored 17 goals in 45 league appearances for Coventry in the 2021–22 season.<ref name = "2021-22"/>

In the [[2022–23 EFL Championship|2022–23 Championship season]], he was named as the player of the month in November after scoring four goals in four games, leading Coventry to four straight wins during that period.<ref name = "Nov22">{{Cite web|url=https://www.efl.com/news/2022/december/sky-bet-efl-manager-and-player-of-the-month-november-winners/|title=Sky Bet EFL Manager and Player of the Month: November Winners|first=Andy|last=Turner|date=8 December 2022|website=CoventryLive}}</ref> Three goals and three assists saw him win the award for a second time in March 2023.<ref name="Mar23 POTM">{{cite web|url=https://www.efl.com/news/2023/april/sky-bet-efl-march-manager-and-player-of-the-month-winners/|title=Sky Bet EFL March Manager and Player of the Month winners!|website=www.efl.com|date=7 April 2023|access-date=9 April 2023}}</ref> Overall he scored 21 goals in 46 appearances, making him the second highest scorer in the league that year. Coventry finished 5th in the table and narrowly missed out on promotion when they lost the [[2023 EFL Championship play-off final|Playoff Final]] on penalties to [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]]. Gyökeres scored his penalty.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-05-26 |title=Coventry City 1–1 Luton Town (5–6 pens): Hatters win shootout to reach Premier League |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65654937 |access-date=2025-07-07 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-gb}}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
On 13 July 2023, Gyökeres signed a five-year contract with [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Sporting CP]], who paid a club record transfer fee of €20 million (plus €4 million in bonuses) for him.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 July 2023 |title=Gyokeres no Sporting: a cláusula de rescisão e todos os valores do negócio |work=O Jogo |trans-title=Gyokeres to Sporting: the release clause and all the values of the deal |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/gyokeres-no-sporting-a-clausula-de-rescisao-e-todos-os-valores-do-negocio-16687236.html |access-date=13 July 2023 |publisher=[[O Jogo]] |language=pt-PT |archive-date=14 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230714134123/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/gyokeres-no-sporting-a-clausula-de-rescisao-e-todos-os-valores-do-negocio-16687236.html |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66139935|title=Coventry striker Gyokeres joins Sporting Lisbon|work=BBC Sport |date=13 July 2023 }}</ref> Coventry are also entitled to payment of 10–15% from a future transfer, and the release clause was set at €100 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 November 2023 |title=Sporting divulga números do mercado de transferências |trans-title=Sporting discloses transfer market numbers |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/sporting-divulga-numeros-do-mercado-de-transferencias-2023111515540109816 |access-date=15 November 2023 |publisher=A Bola |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

====2023–24: Primeira Liga title, Bola de Prata and Player of the Year====
On 12 August, he made his debut for the club, starting and scoring twice in a 3–2 league victory at home to [[F.C. Vizela|Vizela]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/sporting-salvage-three-late-points-after-gyoekeres-stars-in-glowing-debut-38025479|title=Sporting salvage three late points after Gyökeres stars in glowing debut|date=13 August 2023|website=OneFootball}}</ref> On 21 September, Gyökeres made his debut in [[UEFA|European competitions]], starting and scoring in a 2–1 victory away at [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]], in the [[UEFA Europa League]] [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League#Group stage|group stage]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 September 2023 |title=Sporting vence Sturm Graz e quebra maldição austríaca |trans-title=Sporting beats Sturm Graz and breaks Austrian curse |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/liga-europa/artigos/sporting-vence-sturm-graz-e-quebra-maldicao-austriaca |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 26 October, he was shown the first ever red card of his club career, seven minutes into Sporting CP's visit to [[Raków Częstochowa]] in a UEFA Europa League group stage match.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 October 2023 |title=Gyokeres protagoniza expulsão inédita na visita do Sporting à Polónia |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2428133/gyokeres-protagoniza-expulsao-inedita-na-visita-do-sporting-a-polonia |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=Notícias ao Minuto |language=pt}}</ref> On 2 November, on his [[Taça da Liga]] debut, Gyökeres scored a hat-trick in a 4–2 home victory over [[S.C. Farense|Farense]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 November 2023 |title=Sporting bate Farense com hat-trick de Gyökeres |trans-title=Sporting beats Farense with Gyökeres hat-trick |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-nacional/sporting-bate-farense-com-hat-trick-de-gyokeres_d1526553 |access-date=2 November 2023 |publisher=RTP |language=pt-pt}}</ref> Ten days later, he scored in a 2–1 league loss away at [[Lisbon derby|local rivals]] [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Vaza |first=Marco |date=12 November 2023 |title=Afinal, ainda há vida neste Benfica |trans-title=Turns out there is life in this Benfica |url=https://www.publico.pt/2023/11/12/desporto/cronica_de_jogo/golpe-teatro-triunfo-benfica-sporting-2069941 |access-date=13 November 2023 |publisher=Público |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 26 November, in his [[Taça de Portugal]] debut, Gyökeres came on as a second-half substitute and scored Sporting's last goal in an 8–0 home rout over [[Campeonato de Portugal (league)|Campeonato de Portugal]] side Dumiense.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 November 2023 |title=Sporting goleia (8–0) o Dumiense e passa sem problemas aos 'oitavos' da Taça. Paulinho fez hat-trick |trans-title=Sporting thrashes (8–0) Dumiense and advances with no issue to the Cup's round-of-16. Paulinho scored a hat-trick |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/taca-de-portugal/artigos/sporting-goleia-8-0-o-dumiense-e-passa-sem-problemas-aos-oitavos-da-taca-paulinho-fez-hat-trick |access-date=26 November 2023 |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 19 December, he scored and made an assist in a 2–0 league victory at home to [[FC Porto–Sporting CP rivalry|rivals]] [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 December 2023 |title=Sporting vence FC Porto e passa o Natal na frente. Gyokeres brilhou, Pepe foi expulso |trans-title=Sporting beats FC Porto and spends Christmas ahead. Gyokeres shined, Pepe was sent off |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/sporting-vence-fc-porto-e-passa-natal-na-frente-gyokeres-brilhou-pepe-foi-expulso |access-date=19 December 2023 |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

On 5 January 2024, Gyökeres provided four assists in a 5–1 league victory at home to [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=5 January 2024 |title=Sporting 5–1 Estoril: Mão cheia para começar bem o ano |trans-title=Sporting 5–1 Estoril: Handful to start the year well |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/sporting-5-1-estoril-mao-cheia-para-comecar-bem-o-ano-2024010516272758150 |access-date=6 January 2024 |work=[[A Bola]] |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 17 March, he scored his first Primeira Liga hat-trick in a 6–1 victory over [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jn.pt/1056270411/sporting-goleia-o-boavista-com-hat-trick-de-gyokeres-veja-os-golos/ |title=Sporting goleia o Boavista com hat-trick de Gyokeres: veja os golos |publisher=Jornal de Notícias |language=pt |date=17 March 2024 }}</ref> Between September and January, Gyökeres scored thirteen goals and provided six assists, being named the league's Player of the Month and Forward of the Month for five consecutive months. On 29 April, with Sporting two goals down, he scored a brace in the 87th and 88th minutes in a 2–2 draw away against Porto at the ''[[Estádio do Dragão]]'' to ensure Sporting stayed on top of the league table, five points ahead of rivals Benfica.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/martim-fernandes-o-miudo-veloz-de-valongo-que-conquistou-o-dragao-2024042914411075070|title=Martim Fernandes, o miúdo veloz de Valongo que conquistou o Dragão &#124; Abola.pt|date=30 April 2024|website=Abola.pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/3850-porto-2-2-sporting-cp-at-estadio-do-dragao|title=Sporting CP earn a 2–2 draw against Porto in a thriller at Estádio do Dragão|access-date=2 June 2024}}</ref> At the end of the month, Gyökeres was again named the league's Player of the Month and Forward of the Month.

On 5 May, Sporting mathematically secured their 20th Primeira Liga title, following Benfica's defeat to [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]],<ref name=PL2>{{cite web |date=5 May 2024 |title=Sporting sagra-se campeão nacional após derrota do Benfica em Famalicão |trans-title=Sporting become national champions after Benfica's defeat in Famalicão |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/sporting/detalhe/sporting-sagra-se-campeao-nacional-apos-derrota-do-benfica-em-famalicao |access-date=5 May 2024 |website=Record |language=pt}}</ref> and Gyökeres won the [[Bola de Prata (Portugal)|Bola de Prata]] award, after he finished his first season at the club as the [[Bola de Prata (Portugal)|Primeira Liga Top scorer]] with 29 goals, scoring a brace on Sporting's final league match of the season, against [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] on 18 May,<ref>{{cite web |last=Azevedo |first=Rogério |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/noventa-minutos-iguais-a-tres-mil-do-campeonato-cronica-2024051820410700436 |title=Sporting-Chaves, 3–0 Noventa minutos iguais a três mil do campeonato (crónica) |publisher=A Bola |language=pt |date=18 May 2024 }}</ref> to become the second Swedish player to win the top scorer award after [[Mats Magnusson]] in 1989–90.<ref>{{cite web |last=Roseiro |first=Bruno |url=https://observador.pt/2024/05/18/mais-pontos-mais-vitorias-mais-golos-100-de-eficacia-e-um-sueco-goleador-os-10-recordes-para-a-historia-do-20-o-titulo/ |title=Mais pontos, mais vitórias, mais golos, 100% de eficácia e um sueco goleador: os 10 recordes para a história do 20.º título |publisher=Observador |language=pt |date=18 May 2024 }}</ref> He was also named the [[LPFP Primeira Liga Player of the Year|best player of the Primeira Liga]] and was included in the Best XI.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/noticias/kick-off-202122-os-premios-oficiais-e-o-sorteio-dos-campeonatos-ao-minuto-13918176.html|title=Kick-Off 2021/22: os premiados, as declarações e o sorteio dos calendários|website=O Jogo|access-date=8 July 2021|archive-date=20 December 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241220051805/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/noticias/kick-off-202122-os-premios-oficiais-e-o-sorteio-dos-campeonatos-ao-minuto-13918176.html/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 28 May, two days after his appearance for the club in the [[2024 Taça de Portugal Final|Portuguese Cup final]], Gyökeres underwent surgery on his left knee in [[Lisbon]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Roseiro |first=Bruno |title=Uma má notícia que pode ser boa? Viktor Gyökeres falha seleção da Suécia e é operado ao joelho esquerdo |url=https://observador.pt/2024/05/29/uma-ma-noticia-que-pode-ser-boa-viktor-gyokeres-falha-selecao-da-suecia-e-e-operado-ao-joelho-esquerdo/ |access-date=30 May 2024 |website=[[Observador]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

====2024–25: Second consecutive league title, top scorer and departure====
Gyökeres made his return from injury on 3 August 2024, assisting twice in the 4–3 loss to rivals Porto in the [[2024 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/4011-porto-star-in-seven-goal-super-taca-thriller|title=Porto pull off stunning comeback to beat Sporting in seven-goal Super Taça thriller|date=4 August 2024|access-date=4 August 2024|website=PortuGOAL}}</ref> He scored seven times in the four league matches that month, including a hat-trick in a 5–0 win away to [[SC Farense|Farense]] on 23 August. In the process, he became the league highest top scorer in the 21st century, after four matchweeks.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/gyokeres-quebra-mais-um-recorde-goleador-pelo-sporting-na-liga-2024090619285710265|title=Gyokeres quebra mais um recorde goleador pelo Sporting na Liga|date=6 September 2024|access-date=7 September 2024|website=[[A Bola]]}}</ref> Gyökeres also earned the league's Player of the Month and Forward of the Month awards for the month of August.<ref name="auto">{{cite web |date=10 September 2024 |title=Gyökeres also wins the Player of the Month in Liga Portugal Betclic |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20242025/noticias/geral/premios/liga-portugal-betclic/agosto/gyoekeres-arrecada-tambem-premio-de-jogador-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-betclic/ |publisher=Liga Portuguesa de Futebol Profissional |access-date=11 September 2024 |archive-date=13 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241113052458/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20242025/noticias/geral/premios/liga-portugal-betclic/agosto/gyoekeres-arrecada-tambem-premio-de-jogador-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-betclic/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> On 17 September, in his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut, he also scored his first goal in the competition, opening the scoring in their 2–0 victory over [[LOSC Lille|Lille]], being awarded man of the match, during the inaugural matchday of the newly formatted [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |date=17 September 2024 |title=Gyökeres mostrou-se à Europa e Debast fez as pazes com as bancadas |url=https://www.dn.pt/4597849901/gyokeres-mostrou-se-a-europa-e-debast-fez-as-pazes-com-as-bancadas/ |access-date=18 September 2024 |website=[[Diário de Notícias]]|language=pt}}</ref>

On 1 November, Gyökeres scored four goals in a single match during a 5–1 rout against Farense, with his first-half hat-trick tying [[Alberto Acosta|Beto Acosta]]'s feat reached in the [[2000–01 Sporting CP season|2000–01 campaign]].<ref>{{cite web |date=1 November 2024 |title=Hat-trick na primeira parte? Gyökeres iguala Acosta 24 anos depois |url=https://www.zerozero.pt/noticias/playmaker-i-hat-trick-i-na-primeira-parte-gyokeres-iguala-acosta-24-anos-depois/700592 |access-date=3 November 2024 |website=ZeroZero|language=pt}}</ref> Four days later, he became the second Swedish player (after [[Zlatan Ibrahimović]]) and the first Sporting player to score a [[List of UEFA Champions League hat-tricks|hat-trick in the Champions League era]] in a 4–1 victory over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c238450zre1t|title=Sporting 4–1 Manchester City: Viktor Gyokeres hat-trick as Ruben Amorim's side thrash Man City|website=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Baynes |first=Ciaran |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/champions-league/2024-2025/sporting-cp-v-manchester-city-uefa-champions-league-live_sto10387297/story.shtml |title=Sporting CP 4–1 Manchester City: Viktor Gyokeres hat-trick stuns English champions in Ruben Amorim's farewell |publisher=Eurosport |date=5 November 2024 }}</ref> On 16 December, he was awarded the [[Guldbollen|Golden Ball]] (''Guldbollen''), the annual award for best Swedish footballer in 2024.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.svt.se/sport/fotboll/efter-otroliga-malsuccen-viktor-gyokeres-tilldelas-guldbollen-2024|title=Viktor Gyökeres tilldelas Guldbollen 2024|publisher=SVT Sport|author=Ibraheem Alsalman|language=Swedish|date=16 December 2024|accessdate=18 December 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://sverigesradio.se/artikel/guldbollen-till-viktor-gyokeres|title=Guldbollen till Viktor Gyökeres|publisher=Sveriges Radio|author=Andreas Lundin|language=Swedish|date=16 December 2024|accessdate=18 December 2024}}</ref> On 11 January 2025, he scored a penalty in the [[2025 Taça da Liga final|Taça da Liga final]], which Sporting eventually lost on penalties following extra time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20242025/allianzcup/3/1|title=Sporting CP 1:1 SL Benfica|website=Liga Portugal|date=11 January 2025|language=Portuguese|access-date=12 July 2025|archive-date=14 January 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250114180512/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20242025/allianzcup/3/1|url-status=dead}}</ref> By the end of the month, Gyökeres suffered a hamstring injury, leading him to start only one league match during the months of January and February, and missing some crucial games including their final Champions League league phase match against [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] and the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Knockout phase play-offs|knockout phase play-offs]] against [[Borussia Dortmund]], which Sporting ended up losing 3–0 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/viktor-gyokeres/gyokeres/exclusivo-viktor-gyokeres-tem-lesao-no-adutor-esquerdo/20250212/67accbc4d34ef72ee4422a14|title=Exclusivo: Viktor Gyökeres tem lesão no adutor esquerdo|publisher=CNN Portugal|language=Portuguese|date=12 February 2025|accessdate=10 March 2025}}</ref>

On 3 March, Gyökeres scored twice in a 3–1 league victory against Estoril, and with those goals, he became the first player to have scored against every Primeira Liga team, he has faced in a single season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/noticias/24127/gyokeres-completa-o-pleno-contra-equipas-da-liga-portugal-betclic|title=Gyökeres completa o pleno contra equipas da Liga Portugal Betclic|publisher=Liga Portugal|language=Portuguese|date=3 March 2025|accessdate=10 March 2025}}</ref> After two months, he fully recovered from his injury, six days later, adding another brace against [[Casa Pia A.C.|Casa Pia]] by the same scoreline.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2743374/dupla-bala-de-gyokeres-abateu-casa-pia-e-deixou-sporting-isolado-no-trono|title=Dupla bala de Gyökeres abateu Casa Pia e deixou Sporting isolado no trono|publisher=Notícias ao Minuto|language=Portuguese|date=9 March 2025|accessdate=10 March 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://somosfanaticos.fans/pt/sporting/sporting-gyokeres-recuperado-e-hjulmand-esperado-para-a-rececao-ao-estoril-na-liga-portugal|title=Sporting: Gyökeres recuperado e Hjulmand esperado para a receção ao Estoril na Liga Portugal|publisher=Somos Fanáticos|language=Portuguese|date=2 March 2025|accessdate=10 March 2025|archive-date=12 March 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250312164434/https://somosfanaticos.fans/pt/sporting/sporting-gyokeres-recuperado-e-hjulmand-esperado-para-a-rececao-ao-estoril-na-liga-portugal|url-status=dead}}</ref> Hours before the match, it was reported that he made a [[gentlemen's agreement]] with Sporting president [[Frederico Varandas]] that would allow him to leave in the summer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abola.pt/mercado/noticias/fabrizio-romano-confirma-noticia-de-a-bola-sobre-gyokeres-2025031010453381775|title=Fabrizio Romano confirma notícia de A Bola sobre Gyökeres|publisher=A Bola|language=Portuguese|date=10 March 2025|accessdate=10 March 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jn.pt/7870173178/sporting-tera-pacto-com-gyokeres-deixar-sair-o-sueco-abaixo-da-clausula/|title=Sporting terá pacto com Gyökeres: deixar sair o sueco abaixo da cláusula|publisher=Jornal de Notícias|language=Portuguese|date=10 March 2025|accessdate=10 March 2025}}</ref> At the end of the month, Gyökeres was named the Primeira Liga Player of the Month.<ref name="PMP">{{cite news|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/noticias/24445/gyokeres-bisa-como-jogador-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-betclic|title=Gyökeres bisa como Jogador do Mês da Liga Portugal Betclic|publisher=Liga Portugal|language=Portuguese|date=12 April 2025|accessdate=16 April 2025}}</ref> On 27 April, he scored four goals – his second time that season – in a 5–0 league win over Boavista. With his four goals, Gyökeres leapfrogged [[Bas Dost]]'s 93 goals to become the second-highest all-time foreign goalscorer in Sporting's history. He also became the first player to score more than 35 goals in the Primeira Liga since [[Mário Jardel]] in the [[2001–02 Primeira Liga|2001–02 season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.zerozero.pt/noticias/gyokeres-iguala-peyroteo-e-mario-jardel-em-registo-historico-pelo-sporting/799628|title=Gyökeres iguala Peyroteo e Mário Jardel em registo histórico pelo Sporting|publisher=ZeroZero|language=Portuguese|date=21 April 2025|accessdate=29 April 2025}}</ref>

On 10 May, in his 100th appearance for Sporting, he assisted [[Francisco Trincão]]'s goal in a draw against Benfica in the Lisbon derby, which secured Sporting's spot at the top of the league table.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.publico.pt/2025/05/10/desporto/noticia/benficasporting-campeonato-decidese-luz-213264|title=Benfica e Sporting empatam e decisão do título fica para a última jornada|publisher=Publico|language=Portuguese|date=10 May 2025|accessdate=13 May 2025}}{{Dead link|date=January 2026 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref> Seven days later, he scored the winning goal in a 2–0 victory over [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]] as Sporting won the league; this was Gyökeres's second consecutive Primeira League title.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/4763-sporting-beat-vitoria-2-0-to-be-crowned-champions-of-portugal |title=Sporting beat Vitória 2–0 to be crowned champions of Portugal |publisher=PortuGOAL |language=English |date=17 May 2025 |access-date=18 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/noticias/24775/leao-fecha-titulo-com-vitoria |title=Leão fecha título com vitória |publisher=Liga Portugal |language=Portuguese |date=17 May 2025 |access-date=18 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/noticias/24778/sporting-cp-e-bicampeao-da-liga-portugal-betclic |title=Sporting CP é bicampeão da Liga Portugal Betclic |publisher=Liga Portugal |language=Portuguese |date=17 May 2025 |access-date=18 May 2025}}</ref> With 39 goals scored, he finished the season as the Primeira Liga top scorer – for the second consecutive season – also winning his second Bola de Prata and the league's Player of the Year awards.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/todos-os-marcadores-dos-golos-que-deram-o-21o-titulo-ao-sporting-videos-2025051215483911153 |title=Todos os marcadores dos golos que deram o 21.º título ao Sporting (vídeos) |publisher=A Bola |language=Portuguese |date=17 May 2025 |access-date=18 May 2025}}</ref><ref name="PYA">{{cite news|url=https://sapo.pt/artigo/gyokeres-rui-borges-e-quenda-todos-os-premios-da-liga-2024-25-68c1c5868bb55c4ffd4b6c49|title=Gyokeres, Rui Borges e Quenda: todos os prémios da Liga 2024/25|publisher=SAPO|language=Portuguese|date=10 September 2025|accessdate=16 April 2025}}</ref> On 25 May, in the [[2025 Taça de Portugal final|Taça de Portugal final]] against Benfica, he scored from the penalty spot in the 11th minute of added time, to tie the game 1–1 and send it to extra time. Sporting eventually won the match 3–1, winning their first [[Double (association football)|domestic double]] since the [[2001–02 Sporting CP season|2001–02]] season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/articles-video/sporting-cp-wins-2025-ta%C3%A7a-de-portugal-after-extra-time-thriller-vs-benfica-2025-05-25 |title=Sporting CP Wins 2025 Taça de Portugal After Extra-Time Thriller vs Benfica |publisher=Bein Sports |language=English |date=25 May 2025 |access-date=26 May 2025}}</ref>

Following the end of the season, Frederico Varandas confirmed that Gyökeres could leave the club for less than his contractual release clause,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cgj89v9x5yzo|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Sporting striker will not leave for £59m – club president|date=11 June 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> as the player was linked with a transfer to the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cr7zyr5j329o|title=Viktor Gyokeres transfer: Brighton flop to Europe's hot property – what next for Sporting striker?|date=12 June 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

=== Arsenal ===
In late June, [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] made an initial bid of €55 million plus €10 million in bonuses, which was rejected.<ref name="saga">{{Cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/sporting/detalhe/sporting-ameaca-exigir-100-milhoes-por-gyokeres-caso-agente-faca-uso-de-clausula-saiba-qual|title=Sporting ameaça exigir 100 milhões por Gyökeres caso agente faça uso de cláusula — saiba qual|date=11 July 2025|website=Record}}</ref> The clubs continued negotiations in July,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cj61nd0n9rxo|title=Victor Gyokores transfer news: Arsenal in talks to sign striker|date=6 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> with Gyökeres sacrificing part of his salary to facilitate the transfer. After Sporting rejected another bid, he failed to turn up to training for the pre-season, leading him to be disciplined by the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/viktor-gyokeres-arsenal-fc-transfer-news-b1236653.html|title=Gyökeres tells Sporting he will NOT report for training as Arsenal pursuit intensifies|date=11 July 2025|website=Evening Standard}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/sporting/detalhe/arsenal-sobe-a-parada-por-gyokeres-ingleses-oferecem-65-milhoes-mais-15m-em-bonus|title=Arsenal sobe a parada por Gyökeres: ingleses oferecem 65 milhões mais 15 M em bónus|website=Record}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://observador.pt/2025/07/06/arsenal-faz-segunda-proposta-sporting-recusa-mas-gyokeres-ja-nao-volta-a-lisboa-com-uma-duvida-por-resolver/100-milhoes-por-gyokeres-caso-agente-faca-uso-de-clausula-saiba-qual|title=Arsenal faz segunda proposta, Sporting recusa mas Gyökeres já não volta a Lisboa — com uma dúvida por resolver|date=6 July 2025|website=Observador}}{{Dead link|date=January 2026 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2820641/sporting-ja-avisou-gyokeres-que-sabado-e-a-derradeira-oportunidade|title=Sporting já avisou Gyökeres que sábado é a derradeira oportunidade|date=11 July 2025|website=Notícias ao Minuto}}</ref> On 14 July, it was reported that the two clubs had agreed a deal in principle for, with his agent also waiving his fee of the transfer to help facilitate the deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6476054/2025/07/13/arsenal-viktor-gyokeres-transfer/|title=Arsenal step up pursuit of Viktor Gyökeres as Sporting set deadline|date=13 July 2025|website=The Athletic (via The New York Times)}}</ref> The transfer was delayed due to issues with add-ons to the deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c8d6vj0759mo|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Arsenal on the verge of completing deal for Sporting striker|date=22 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 25 July, it was reported that Gyökeres was to undergo a medical at Arsenal after being given permission to travel to England by Sporting.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6510398/2025/07/25/arsenal-transfer-viktor-gyokeres-sporting-deal/|title=Arsenal reach full agreement with Sporting CP for Viktor Gyökeres – initial €63.5m plus €10m in add-ons|last=Ornstein|first=David|website=The Athletic|publisher=The New York Times Company|date=25 July 2025|access-date=25 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cnvmvp6e9gro|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Arsenal set to complete signing within 48 hours|date=25 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

The following day, Gyökeres signed for Arsenal for a fee of £55 million, potentially rising to £63.5 million with add-ons, signing a five-year deal with the club.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Viktor Gyokeres joins Arsenal: Sporting striker completes transfer to Premier League club signing five-year deal |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11670/13401260/viktor-gyokeres-joins-arsenal-sporting-striker-completes-transfer-to-premier-league-club-signing-five-year-deal |date=26 July 2025 |access-date=26 July 2025 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cjrljv22d53o|title=Viktor Gyokeres signs for Arsenal: Will Swedish striker help Arsenal to Premier League title?|date=26 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He said he wanted to join the club after losing to them with Sporting the previous season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c860l3d10j6o|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Arsenal sign Sweden striker from Sporting|date=26 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> After his signing, some analysts and pundits, such as [[Rio Ferdinand]], questioned if Gyökeres would be successful for Arsenal, due to previous goal scoring struggles for other formerly prolific forwards moving from the Primeira Liga to the Premier League (such as Mário Jardel), and Gyökeres' previous struggle to break into the first team at Brighton.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c07d34mg321o|title=Portugal to Premier League moves – how will Gyokeres compare to other transfers?|date=27 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 27 July, Gyökeres was unveiled as an Arsenal player before a pre-season game against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in Singapore.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c9vd8zgvm71o|title=Arsenal 3–2 Newcastle: Viktor Gyokeres unveiled and Max Dowman impresses in Gunners win|date=27 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> After being given squad number 14, previously worn by [[Thierry Henry]] (Arsenal's all-time leading goalscorer), Gyökeres said that he did not want to be compared to Henry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cn84gv4n18ko|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Arsenal signing on taking Thierry Henry's number 14 shirt|first=Alex|last=Howell|date=30 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

==== 2025–26: Debut season ====
Following pre-season, Arsenal manager [[Mikel Arteta]] said that Gyökeres "will be 100% or more" ready for the opening game of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ckgj2vqd0zqo|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Sweden striker will '100% be ready' for Premier League start|first=Alex|last=Howell|date=6 August 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 17 August, Gyökeres started in the opening game at [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] as Arsenal won 1–0, but he was subbed off in favor of [[Kai Havertz]] after just under an hour of play after failing to make much of an impact.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Anka |first=Carl |last2=de Roché |first2=Art |last3=Walid |first3=Ahmed |date=18 August 2025 |title=Man Utd 0 Arsenal 1: Analysing Arsenal's 'new' set piece, Amorim's goalkeeper problem, watching Gyokeres and Sesko |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6556019/2025/08/17/man-utd-arsenal-highlights/ |access-date=18 August 2025 |work=[[The New York Times]] |department=[[The Athletic]]}}</ref> However, in the following match against newly promoted [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], Gyökeres scored a brace, one of which was a penalty, as Arsenal defeated Leeds 5–0.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |date=23 August 2025 |title=Arsenal put five past Leeds but lose Ødegaard and Saka to injury |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/aug/23/arsenal-leeds-premier-league-match-report |access-date=23 August 2025 |work=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> In September, he won the [[Gerd Müller Trophy]], part of the [[2025 Ballon d'Or|Ballon d'Or Awards show]], for scoring the most goals, 63 in total, for both European clubs and national teams, the previous season.<ref name="auto6">{{Cite web |last=Peat |date=23 September 2025 |title=At tonight's Ballon d'Or Awards, Viktor Gyokeres has received the Gerd Muller Trophy for his sensational campaign for club and country in 2024/25.|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/viktor-gyokeres-wins-gerd-muller-trophy|access-date=23 September 2025 |website=arsenal.com |language=en}}</ref> After his first 10 Arsenal games, Gyökeres had scored 3 goals, all of which came in his first 4 games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cdx2750g617o|title=Ten games, three goals – assessing Viktor Gyokeres' start at Arsenal|first=Alex|last=Howell|date=6 October 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 21 October, Gyökeres scored two goals in a 4–0 win against [[Atlético Madrid]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league stage]], opening up his European account for Arsenal and ending the goal drought.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx27gdvd3zlo|title=Arsenal 4–0 Atletico Madrid: Glenn Murray on Viktor Gyokeres' goals|date=22 October 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 1 November, Gyökeres scored in a 2–0 win against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], but suffered a hamstring injury later on in that game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c5ylqnde48do|title=Arsenal injury news: Mikel Arteta 'concerned' by Viktor Gyokeres injury|first=Alex|last=Howell|date=3 November 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/ckgkj724kk8o|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Arsenal striker may have injured hamstring and is set for further scans|first=Sami|last=Mokbel|date=4 November 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> After being sidelined for nearly a month, he returned from injury on 30 November, coming on as a substitute against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=James |first1=Josh |title=Match report: Chelsea 1–1 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Nov-30/chelsea-1-1-arsenal-match-report |website=arsenal.com |date=30 November 2025}}</ref>

In February 2026, he was described by the BBC as "one of the Premier League's most in-form players", being the top scorer in the Premier League in the 2026 calendar year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c8d5jezj7y9o|title=Viktor Gyokeres: Has Arsenal forward finally found form?|first=Alex|last=Howell|date=10 February 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> In early May 2026 Gyökeres scored his 20th goal of the season, the first time an Arsenal player had reached that tally in their debut season since [[Alexis Sánchez]] in the [[2014–15 Arsenal F.C. season|2014–15 season]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cdjp3v7lv8mo|title=Arsenal: Has Viktor Gyokeres proved his critics wrong?|first=Alex|last=Howell|date=2 May 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> with Arsenal winning the [[2025–26 Premier League]] title a few weeks later.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Robson |first=James |date=2026-05-19 |title=Arsenal wins its first Premier League title in 22 years after Man City draws with Bournemouth |url=https://apnews.com/article/man-city-bournemouth-arsenal-premier-league-title-tottenham-828b9b177f8c0484754945eeb4ee0d0f |access-date=2026-05-19 |website=AP News |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Gyökeres played youth football for Sweden at [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21]] level.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/landslag/landslagsdatabas/landslagsspelare/?fplid=59352c5f-18f4-4c78-9a6f-28d618956855|title=Viktor Gyökeres — svenskfotboll.se|website=www2.svenskfotboll.se|access-date=23 March 2019|archive-date=24 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230124224344/https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/landslag/landslagsdatabas/landslagsspelare/?fplid=59352c5f-18f4-4c78-9a6f-28d618956855|url-status=dead}}</ref> Gyökeres featured regularly for [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|Sweden]] in the nation's [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification|qualification campaign]] for the [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] during which he scored twice, including the winning goal against [[Italy national under-19 football team|Italy]] to help Sweden qualify for the tournament for the first time.<ref name="AB" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/news/0257-0dee4cc0dc2c-dd57cafd21e6-1000--ten-to-follow-from-under-19s/|title=Ten to follow from Under-19s|website=UEFA|last=Haslam|first=Andrew|date=17 July 2017|access-date=7 January 2018}}</ref> He was then selected for the squad which took part in the tournament in Georgia and scored in all three of Sweden's group matches but was unable to help the nation progress to the knockout stages of the tournament. His return of three goals later saw him share the Golden Boot award with [[England national under-19 football team|England]]'s [[Ben Brereton]] and [[Ryan Sessegnon]], and the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands]]' [[Joël Piroe]].<ref name="U19">{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/news/0257-0dee4c569eb6-4f5ed8230d55-1000--four-share-under-19-top-scorers-prize/|title=Four share Under-19 top scorers' prize|website=UEFA|date=15 July 2017|access-date=5 January 2017}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 8 January 2019, Gyökeres made his senior international debut for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] in a 1–0 loss against [[Finland national football team|Finland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/KvJryy|first=Per|last=Bohman|title="Vi har inte många som honom i svensk fotboll"|website=Aftonbladet|date=8 January 2019|language=sv}}</ref> Three days later, Gyökeres scored his first senior goal for Sweden in a 2–2 draw against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/international-friendlies/2019/live-sweden-iceland_mtc1088377/live.shtml|title=Live: Sweden vs. Iceland {{!}} International friendlies|date=11 January 2019|website=Eurosport|location=United Kingdom|access-date=12 January 2019}}</ref> In October 2021, after scoring nine goals in 11 [[EFL Championship]] games for Coventry, Gyökeres was called up to the Sweden national team to replace [[Zlatan Ibrahimović]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2022 World Cup qualifying matches]] against [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] and [[Greece national football team|Greece]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coventrytelegraph.net/sport/football/football-news/coventry-city-gyokeres-ibrahimovic-sweden-21745673|title=Sky Blues' Viktor Gyokeres to replace Ibrahimovic for Sweden|first=Andy|last=Turner|date=2 October 2021|website=CoventryLive}}</ref> On 16 October 2023, Gyökeres had given Sweden a 15th-minute lead before [[Romelu Lukaku]] equalised in an away game against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]], when the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifier]] was abandoned at half-time following an [[2023 Brussels shooting|Islamist-related fatal shooting in Brussels]] that targeted and killed two Swedes outside the stadium.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 October 2023 |title=Soccer match between Belgium and Sweden suspended after a gunman kills 2 Swedes in Brussels |url=https://apnews.com/article/belgium-sweden-match-abandoned-brussels-shooting-05041c1e11d896285ab329b15428d6b4|work=[[Associated Press News]]|access-date=24 October 2023}}</ref>

On 16 November 2024, he scored the first goal in a 2–1 victory against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]], helping Sweden clinch promotion to [[2026–27 UEFA Nations League|League B]] of the [[UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://apnews.com/article/nations-league-germany-netherlands-c3ee2665526b3bf7de6bff0df751d5ed |title=Gyökeres leads Sweden to Nations League win and the Dutch reach the knockout rounds|work=[[Associated Press News]] |date=16 November 2024 |access-date=20 November 2024}}</ref> Three days later, Gyökeres scored four goals in a 6–0 [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|Nations League]] home win over [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]], completing his first international hat-trick in the process.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/nov/19/nations-league-gyokeres-scores-four-for-sweden-in-rout-of-azerbaijan |title=Nations League: Gyökeres scores four for Sweden in rout of Azerbaijan |website=[[The Guardian]] |date=19 November 2024 |access-date=20 November 2024}}</ref>

On 26 March 2026, Gyökeres scored a hat-trick when Sweden beat [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] 3–1 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round#Path B|2026 FIFA World Cup play-off semi-final]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/czexpdw8n32o|title= Gyokeres Sweden's hero as Kosovo dream of first World Cup|date=26 March 2026|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=27 March 2026}}</ref> Five days later, on 31 March, Gyökeres would score the winning goal in a 3–2 victory over [[Poland national football team|Poland]] in the World Cup qualifying playoff final, returning Sweden to the World Cup after failing to qualify for 2022 edition of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c8dl97er10lt|title=Sweden 3–2 Poland: Viktor Gyökeres winner fires Graham Potter's side to World Cup |first=Sam |last=Drury|date=31 March 2026 |website=BBC Sport|accessdate=31 March 2026}}</ref>

In May 2026, he was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] by head coach [[Graham Potter]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c3r29z5yz79o|title=Sweden World Cup squad: Alexander Isak and Viktor Gyokeres among those selected|date=12 May 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

== Player profile ==
=== Style of play ===
Gyökeres is known for his physicality, pace, and stamina,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Young-Myles |first=Oliver |date=26 May 2023 |title=Coventry's 'natural finisher' Gyokeres is ready for the top flight after Brighton woes |url=https://inews.co.uk/sport/football/viktor-gyokeres-coventry-premier-league-brighton-struggles-2368031 |access-date=25 October 2023 |website=inews.co.uk |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=27 May 2023|title=Viktor Gyökeres: The Making of a Coventry Cult Hero|url=https://theanalyst.com/2023/05/viktor-gyokeres-coventry-city-cult-hero|access-date=11 November 2024 |website=Opta Analyst|language=en}}</ref> using his acceleration to exploit space behind defenders and his strength to act as a target man in aerial duels and ground battles.<ref name=SOP>{{Cite web |date=1 August 2024|title=Viktor Gyökeres position and style of play |url=https://learning.coachesvoice.com/cv/viktor-gyokeres-sporting-sweden/ |access-date=11 November 2024 |website=Coaches' Voice |language=en}}</ref> He excels in both aerial duels and on the ground, using his strength and size to shield the ball and link play, often contributing by running the channels or delivering crosses, while also being capable of creating chances through sharp turns and flicks in one-on-one situations.<ref name=SP2>{{Cite web |date=4 January 2024|title=Viktor Gyökeres: Sweden's Next Top Striker|url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/viktor-gyokeres-swedens-next-top-striker/|access-date=11 November 2024 |website=Breaking The Lines|language=en}}</ref><ref name=SP1>{{Cite web |date=3 September 2023|title=Viktor Gyökeres Scouting Report: Sporting CP's Silver Ball Contender|url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/viktor-gyokeres-202324-scout-report-tactical-analysis-tactics |access-date=11 November 2024 |website=Total Football Analysis|language=en}}</ref> His pressing ability helps him disrupt opposition build-up and force defensive mistakes, helping also in set-piece situations.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 August 2024|title=Arsenal's Ultimate Necessity of Viktor Gyökeres|url=https://medium.com/@benedictosembiring/arsenals-ultimate-necessity-of-viktor-gy%C3%B6keres-8ff9fc16af09 |website=Medium|language=en}}</ref>

At Sporting CP's [[Formation (association football)#3–4–3|3–4–3]] formation, he played as the [[Striker (association football)|central striker]] positioned at the highest point in the attack to lead the offensive line.<ref name=SP1/> He often makes runs into the box and uses his physical presence to challenge defenders, pulling them out of position to create space for the wide forwards.<ref name=SP1/> Gyökeres also drifts into the wings or half-spaces to help stretch the opposition's defense.<ref name=SP1/><ref name=SOP/> His link-up play involves holding the ball and distributing it to teammates, creating opportunities through his movement and positioning.<ref name=SP1/><ref name=SOP/>

===Goal celebration===
Gyökeres celebrates his goals by crossing both of his hands over his mouth; his former Coventry City teammate [[Josh Eccles]] said: "I think the celebration is because of the character in the film [<nowiki/>[[Hannibal Lecter]]]. He eats people and Viktor destroys defences."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Abola.pt |date=15 October 2023 |title=Sporting: revelado o mistério da celebração de Gyokeres {{!}} Abola.pt |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/sporting-revelado-o-misterio-da-celebracao-de-gyokeres-2023101523113179332 |access-date=25 October 2023 |website=Abola.pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Máscara nos golos de Gyokeres inspirada no filme 'Silêncio dos Inocentes' |url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/mascara-nos-golos-de-gyokeres-inspirada-no-filme-silencio-dos-inocentes |access-date=25 October 2023 |website=www.cmjornal.pt |date=14 October 2023 |language=pt-PT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Turner |first=Andy |date=20 March 2023 |title=Coventry City notebook: Kyle's kid gloves Vik celebration theory emerges |url=https://www.coventrytelegraph.net/sport/football/football-news/coventry-city-notebook-viktor-gyokeres-26516435 |access-date=25 October 2023 |website=Coventry Live |language=en}}</ref> According to Swedish newspaper ''[[Aftonbladet]]'' in November 2023, Gyökeres said: "There were lots of guesses... It was this [Hannibal Lecter] and [[Batman]] and everything possible, but nobody got it right. No one came close. Yes, it's a secret. I can clarify that, but not today."<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 November 2023 |title=Gyökeres slår tillbaka om målgesten: "Är fel" |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/JQ9VpX |access-date=19 November 2023 |website=www.aftonbladet.se |language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 November 2023 |title=Gyökeres fala do festejo curioso e aborda o futuro: "Acabei de chegar..." |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2440797/gyokeres-fala-do-festejo-curioso-e-aborda-o-futuro-acabei-de-chegar |access-date=19 November 2023 |website=Notícias ao Minuto |language=pt}}</ref>

On 18 December 2023, in an interview for [[Sport TV]] after a 2–0 league victory at home to rivals Porto, he was questioned about his usual goal celebration and answered: "I thought you'd ask me sooner. I've been here for a few months and no one has asked me that question... I'll tell you after the season if we win the league... no problem."<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 December 2023 |title=Gyokeres revela quando vai explicar famoso festejo |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/gyokeres-revela-quando-vai-explicar-famoso-festejo-2023121909394688229 |access-date=19 December 2023 |website=Abola.pt |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Gyokeres: "Não sei porque não contou o segundo golo" | date=18 December 2023 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UoshR8K4Xtc |access-date=1 January 2024 |language=en}}</ref> In June 2024, the Portuguese media claimed the goal celebrations were inspired by [[Bane (DC Comics)|Bane]], a comics character, after Gyökeres has posted on Instagram a phrase attributed to Bane.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Roseiro |first=Bruno |title=Não, não era por Hannibal Lecter: Gyökeres explica "máscara" nos festejos (que é de um vilão da trilogia do "Cavaleiro das Trevas") |url=https://observador.pt/2024/06/25/nao-nao-era-por-hannibal-lecter-gyokeres-explica-mascara-nos-festejos-que-e-de-um-vilao-da-trilogia-do-cavaleiro-das-trevas/ |access-date=15 July 2024 |website=Observador |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Gyökeres is of [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] descent through his paternal grandfather who emigrated to Sweden,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/a/yEK59E/viktor-gyokeres-om-flytt-till-premier-league-det-lockar |title="Klart det lockar med PL – får se när det är dags"|author=Simon Bank|date=17 December 2024|website=Sportbladet |access-date=20 December 2024}}</ref> and is a dual citizen of Hungary and Sweden.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nsk.se/artikel/valde-sverige-drabbad-av-hat-i-sociala-medier/ |title=Valde Sverige – drabbad av hat i sociala medier|author=TT |date=31 May 2022|website=Norra Skåne|access-date=20 December 2024}}</ref> His father Stefan Gyökeres played football for [[IFK Östersund]] and [[Stuguns BK|Stugun]] in the 1980s and 1990s.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nyheter24.se/sport/1240570-allt-om-viktor-gyokeres-pappa-klubbar-och-exflickvan |title=Allt om Viktor Gyökeres: Pappa, klubbar och exflickvän|author=Johan Åkesson|date=13 February 2024|website=Nyheter24|access-date=22 December 2024}}</ref>

Broadcaster [[CMTV]] reported in January 2024 that Gyökeres was in a relationship with Portuguese actress {{ill|Inês Aguiar|pt}}.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ferreira |first=Diogo |date=3 January 2024 |title=Viktor Gyökeres do Sporting "rouba" o coração da atriz portuguesa Inês Aguiar |url=https://dioguinho.com/viktor-gyokeres-do-sporting-rouba-o-coracao-da-atriz-portuguesa-ines-aguiar/ |access-date=3 January 2024 |website=Dioguinho |language=pt-PT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Viktor Gyokeres e Ivo Lucas, namorados das gémeas Aguiar, já são amigos |url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/famosos/detalhe/viktor-gyokeres-e-ivo-lucas-namorados-das-gemeas-aguiar-ja-sao-amigos |access-date=13 April 2024 |website=www.cmjornal.pt |language=pt-PT |archive-date=7 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240507004609/https://www.cmjornal.pt/famosos/detalhe/viktor-gyokeres-e-ivo-lucas-namorados-das-gemeas-aguiar-ja-sao-amigos |url-status=dead }}</ref> He was formerly in a relationship with fellow professional footballer [[Amanda Nildén]], who he met in high school,<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 October 2021 |title=Superparet gör succé – hinner inte träffas: "Tuffaste perioden" |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/8QEr8W/superparet-gor-succe--hinner-inte-traffas-tuffaste-perioden |access-date=13 October 2024 |website=www.aftonbladet.se |language=sv}}</ref> and who joined the [[Brighton & Hove Albion W.F.C.|Brighton women's team]] when Gyökeres moved to the club in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/sport/fotboll/viktor-gyokeres-om-flytten-till-premier-league/|title=Gyökeres till Premier League – flickvännen kan gå till samma klubb|trans-title=Gyökeres to the Premier League – girlfriend can go to the same club|website=SVT Sport|last=Kurt|first=Nemrud|date=3 January 2018|access-date=7 January 2018}}</ref>

